#Text=The newly introduced graph classification datasets are available at \[SNAP\](https://snap.stanford.edu/data/#disjointgraphs), \[TUD Graph Kernel Datasets\](https://ls11-www.cs.tu-dortmund.de/staff/morris/graphkerneldatasets), and \[GraphLearning.io\](https://chrsmrrs.github.io/datasets/).  --------------------------------------------------------------  \*\*Citing\*\*  If you find \*Karate Club\* and the new datasets useful in your research, please consider citing the following paper:  ```bibtex @inproceedings{karateclub,        title = {{Karate Club: An API Oriented Open-source Python Framework for Unsupervised Learning on Graphs}},        author = {Benedek Rozemberczki and Oliver Kiss and Rik Sarkar},        year = {2020},        pages = {3125–3132},        booktitle = {Proceedings of the 29th ACM International Conference on Information and Knowledge Management (CIKM '20)},        organization = {ACM}, } ``` ----------------------------------------------------------------  \*\*A simple example\*\*  \*Karate Club\* makes the use of modern community detection techniques quite easy (see \[here\](https://karateclub.readthedocs.io/en/latest/notes/introduction.html) for the accompanying tutorial).
